Hello, I had never seen a jenna marbles video until today, and that time my baby brother showed me a video of her other grey dog crying but I think it was like a meme compilation; so I think I might start doing that now since this is her last video of the decade. Good of her taking vacations during these holidays and be so super casual about it.

I don't I've always liked people based on how they treat animals and this girls right here, she's doing the most in something that most of us, who have pets, wouldn't think about a lot. Her voice, the music, the way she kept reassuring their dog, it goes to show how much of a loving, patient person she is; that's the content I want to watch, anyway if anyone made it this far- happy holidays, you're loved and wanted, you don't need or believe all the rude things relatives say at this holidays parties- you're better than that; and if you're on a shitty situation, believe me, even if it sounds stupid, too hard, or just straight up cliche- it does get better, it will get better

-your local trans
